{{Lunisolar October|qq=}} 
'''October 30''' is the 30th day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} . 

As with all other days 30 of the Sino-Japanese calendar it sometimes happens and sometimes does not depending on the lunar cycle.<ref>https://www.ndl.go.jp/koyomi/e/history/index.html</ref> Months are annotated as either long ({{zh|c=大|l=big|qq=}}  for months with 30 days) or short ({{zh|c=小|l=small|qq=}}  for months with 29 days). There are also other elements of the traditional Chinese calendar.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref>

== Events ==

== Births ==
* {{ill|Keichō|ja|Keichō|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ([[Gregorian calendar]]   {{ill|1596|ja|1596|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 19|ja|12月19日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ） - {{ill|Matsudaira Nobutsuna|ja|松平信綱|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 、{{ill|Edo Shogunate|ja|Tokugawa shogunate|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|Rōchū|ja|老中|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} （+ {{ill|1662|ja|1662|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ）
* {{ill|Kangxi|ja|Kangxi|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 17th year ([[Gregorian calendar]]   {{ill|1678|ja|1678|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 3|ja|12月3日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ） - {{ill|Emperor Yongzheng|ja|雍正帝|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 、{{ill|Qing dynasty|ja|清|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} の5代{{ill|Emperor|ja|Emperor|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} （+ {{ill|1735|ja|1735|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ）

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Tenshō (Japan)|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 12nd year ([[Gregorian calendar]]   {{ill|1584|ja|1584|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 8|ja|11月8日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ） - {{ill|Ashina Moritaka|ja|蘆名盛隆|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , {{ill|Sengoku daimyo|ja|戦国大名|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  (* {{ill|1561|ja|1561|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} )
* {{ill|Shōtoku (era)|ja|正徳|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ([[Gregorian calendar]]   {{ill|1715|ja|1715|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 1|ja|11月1日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ） - {{ill|Shibukawa Harumi|ja|渋川春海|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , also known as the 2nd {{ill|Yasui Santetsu|ja|安井算哲|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , astronomer and calendrical scholar (* {{ill|1639|ja|1639|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} )
* {{ill|Enkyō (Japan)|ja|Enkyō|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]]   {{ill|1747|ja|1747|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 8|ja|11月8日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ） - {{ill|Terazaka Nobuyuki|ja|寺坂信行|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , one of the {{ill|Forty-seven rōnin|ja|赤穂浪士|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  (* {{ill|1665|ja|1665|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} )
